,0.10684,0.096526,0.082254,0.071546,0.066978,0.052479,0.035204],"unified_progress":[0.07178,0.10372,0.074526,0.10402,0.10547,0.1033,0.09266,0.087781,0.078054,0.070781,0.060462,0.047445]},{"section":8,"text":"Hmm, that kind of murmur can be linked to several conditions.","dimension":0,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.044944,0.10574,0.1171,0.12038,0.11442,0.1082,0.097138,0.081385,0.074439,0.061755,0.047225,0.027283],"unified_progress":[0.047164,0.088001,0.10225,0.10534,0.11204,0.10307,0.10009,0.088451,0.081068,0.070109,0.05959,0.042833]},{"section":9,"text":"It might mean there's some blood flow issue between the chambers of the heart or around the valves.","dimension":4,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.044156,0.067308,0.089919,0.10754,0.11292,0.1124,0.10753,0.09643,0.086565,0.079578,0.061284,0.03436],"unified_progress":[0.048205,0.072912,0.088776,0.10001,0.1019,0.1017,0.099601,0.096801,0.090363,0.082229,0.067475,0.050036]},{"section":10,"text":"But wait, let's not jump to conclusions just yet.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.12263,0.098799,0.091979,0.081831,0.081151,0.080725,0.080474,0.086314,0.075889,0.050302,0.05165,0.098256],"unified_progress":[0.21161,0.080831,0.064819,0.065674,0.075308,0.073459,0.09528,0.081249,0.077414,0.06158,0.057551,0.055226]},{"section":11,"text":"The doctor did an ECG, and it showed a short P-R interval with a slow upstroke of the QRS complex.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037088,0.071936,0.10237,0.12524,0.13037,0.12165,0.10638,0.086233,0.07035,0.063649,0.050117,0.034607],"unified_progress":[0.04989,0.085826,0.076721,0.10971,0.11448,0.10802,0.099121,0.09268,0.080388,0.072463,0.06186,0.048841]},{"section":12,"text":"Oh, that's interesting.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.12542,0.1019,0.094265,0.082992,0.083656,0.083225,0.080965,0.084712,0.073052,0.048473,0.048712,0.092632],"unified_progress":[0.2185,0.085325,0.069167,0.06711,0.07802,0.074191,0.086898,0.079501,0.07464,0.05949,0.054883,0.052273]},{"section":13,"text":"A short P-R interval usually means the electrical signal from the atria to the ventricles is traveling quickly.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046014,0.063942,0.084824,0.10193,0.10752,0.10796,0.10405,0.093981,0.087099,0.085047,0.068905,0.048728],"unified_progress":[0.056521,0.08131,0.067624,0.10262,0.10544,0.10573,0.097993,0.094013,0.085999,0.079224,0.067824,0.055699]},{"section":14,"text":"This can happen if there's something like Wolff-Parkinson-White syndrome, where there are extra pathways in the heart that allow signals to bypass the normal route.","dimension":7,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031305,0.04669,0.065646,0.083492,0.096694,0.10642,0.1124,0.11042,0.10977,0.11057,0.08201,0.044571],"unified_progress":[0.037343,0.060023,0.08262,0.094371,0.099215,0.11072,0.1041,0.099456,0.094353,0.086975,0.072265,0.058558]},{"section":15,"text":"So, putting all these clues together\u2014the super-fast heart rate, the specific type of murmur, and the ECG findings\u2014it seems like Wolff-Parkinson-White syndrome fits perfectly here.","dimension":8,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.019943,0.038173,0.052468,0.063961,0.073048,0.080765,0.088438,0.093315,0.10192,0.11778,0.14026,0.12992],"unified_progress":[0.030631,0.049812,0.062793,0.074727,0.082015,0.093221,0.092871,0.09697,0.10042,0.10221,0.10753,0.1068]},{"section":16,"text":"It's known for causing episodes of really fast heart rates due to those extra electrical pathways.","dimension":7,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026091,0.036782,0.048301,0.060789,0.073111,0.085406,0.097823,0.10432,0.11485,0.13131,0.12703,0.09418],"unified_progress":[0.032586,0.049747,0.065696,0.076204,0.085968,0.096774,0.099022,0.10256,0.10329,0.10254,0.097193,0.088416]},{"section":17,"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","dimension":-1,"grou